ElementType.name: commandButton
ElementType.description: Extends standard commandButton by user role support.

ElementType.name: commandLink
ElementType.description: Extends standard commandLink by user role support and the HTML target attribute.

ElementType.name: dataTable
ElementType.description: Extended data_table that adds some additional features to the standard data_table action: see attribute descriptions for preserveDataModel, sortColumn, sortAscending and preserveSort.

ElementType.name: inputHidden
ElementType.description: Extends standard inputHidden by providing additional MyFaces goodies.

ElementType.name: inputText
ElementType.description: Extends standard inputText by user role support.

ElementType.name: inputTextarea
ElementType.description: Extends standard inputTextarea by user role support.

ElementType.name: message
ElementType.description: MyFaces extension to the standard messages tag: see summaryDetailSeparator attribute

ElementType.name: messages
ElementType.description: MyFaces extension to the standard messages tag: see showInputLabel attribute

ElementType.name: outputLabel
ElementType.description: Extends standard outputLabel by user role support.

ElementType.name: outputText
ElementType.description: Extends standard outputText by user role support.

ElementType.name: panelGroup
ElementType.description: Extends standard panelGroup by user role support.

ElementType.name: selectOneMenu
ElementType.description: Extends standard selectOneMenu by user role support.

ElementType.name: selectOneRadio
ElementType.description: Extends standard selectOneRadio by user role support. Additionally this extended selectOneRadio accepts a layout attribute of value "spread" (see custom radio tag).

ElementType.name: selectManyCheckbox
ElementType.description: Extends standard selectManyCheckbox by user role support. Additionally this extended selectManyCheckbox accepts a layout attribute of value "spread" (see custom checkbox tag).

ElementType.name: inputCalendar
ElementType.description: Provides a calendar.

ElementType.name: jsValueChangeListener
ElementType.description: Value change listener on client side.

ElementType.name: jsValueSet
ElementType.description: Setting a value from the model in java-script so that it can be used (e.g. by the value change listener) afterwards.

ElementType.name: checkbox
ElementType.description: Renders a HTML input of type "checkbox". The associated SelectItem comes from an extended selectManyCheckbox component with layout "spread". The selectManyCheckbox is referenced by the "for" attribute. All HTML pass-through attributes for this input are taken from the associated selectManyCheckbox.

ElementType.name: commandNavigation
ElementType.description: Must be nested inside a panel_navigation action and renders a clickable navigation item. This action is derived from the standard command_link action and has equal attributes. (Replaces former "navigation_item" tag.)

ElementType.name: commandSortHeader
ElementType.description: Clickable sort column header. Must be nested inside an extended data_table tag. This tag is derived from the standard command_link tag and has the additional attributes columnName and arrow. Note: In contrary to normal command links the default for the "immediate" attribute is "true".

ElementType.name: dataList
ElementType.description: Similar to dataTable, but does not render a table. Instead the layout attribute controls how each dataRow is rendered.

ElementType.name: dataScroller
ElementType.description: Scroller for UIData components eg. dataTable Must be nested inside footer facet of dataTable OR for attribute must be given so that corresponding uiData can be found

ElementType.name: inputFileUpload
ElementType.description: You must enable the MultiPart Filter to make this component work (see web.xml). Also, don't forget to set the form's attribute "enctype" to "multipart/form-data". See "examples/web/fileupload.jsp" for an example!

ElementType.name: inputHtml
ElementType.description: An inline HTML based word processor based on the Kupu library. See http://kupu.oscom.org Right now, the support is limited to one editor per page (but you can use tabs to have multiple editors, but only one rendered at a time).

ElementType.name: selectOneCountry
ElementType.description: A localized list of countries choose box. The value binds to the country ISO 3166 code. This is the same code as for java.util.Locale.getCountry(). The official codes list is available here : http://www.iso.ch/iso/en/prods-services/iso3166ma/02iso-3166-code-lists/list-en1.html

ElementType.name: stylesheet
ElementType.description: a component, which renders the path to a common CSS-file

ElementType.name: div
ElementType.description: Places a div around its children

ElementType.name: radio
ElementType.description: Renders a HTML input of type "radio". The associated SelectItem comes from an extended selectOneRadio component with layout "spread". The selectOneRadio is referenced by the "for" attribute. All HTML pass-through attributes for this input are taken from the associated selectOneRadio.

ElementType.name: treeColumn
ElementType.description: Renders a HTML input of type "treeColumn". This tag outlines the column where the tree structure will be render as part of the tree table.

ElementType.name: treeCheckbox
ElementType.description: Renders a HTML input of type "treeCheckbox". The associated comes from the treeCheckbox itemLabel and itemValue. The selected items come from an extended selectManyCheckbox component with layout "spread". The selectManyCheckbox is referenced by the "for" attribute. All HTML pass-through attributes for this input are taken from the associated selectManyCheckbox.

ElementType.name: popup
ElementType.description: Renders a popup which displays on a mouse event.

ElementType.name: newspaperTable
ElementType.description: A data table for rendering long skinny tables as short wide table by wrapping the table over a specified number of columns.

ElementType.name: aliasBean
ElementType.description:
A tag that defines a new bean (alias) with a given value. This allows you to design a subform with a generic (fictive) beans and to include it in all the pages where you use it. You just need to make an alias to the real bean named after the generic bean before including the subform.
When used within an aliasBeansScope tag, this tag adds the alias to the aliasBeansScope. This makes configuration with multiple aliasBeans easier to write.

ElementType.name: saveState
ElementType.description: saveState enables you to persist beans and values longer than request scope, but shorter than session scope. It is ideal for persisting backing beans and values with the same scope as your view components. It does this by saving the target state with the component tree.

ElementType.name: updateActionListener
ElementType.description: Registers a org.apache.myfaces.custom.updateactionlistener.UpdateActionListener at the parent component.

ElementType.name: validateCreditCard
ElementType.description: A custom validator for creditCards, based upons Jakarta Commons.

ElementType.name: validateEmail
ElementType.description: A custom validator for email address format, based upons Jakarta Commons.

ElementType.name: validateRegExpr
ElementType.description: A custom validator for reg. expr., based upons Jakarta Commons.

ElementType.name: validateEqual
ElementType.description: A custom validator for validations against foreign component values.
